File::HomeDir::Tiny, version 0.01

This module provides a single function, ‘home’, returning the current
user’s home directory.


INSTALLATION

The easiest way to install this module is to use the CPAN  module  or
the cpan script:

    [sudo] perl -MCPAN -e "install File::HomeDir::Tiny"

    [sudo] cpan File::HomeDir::Tiny

Or you can use the following:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    [sudo] make install


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires perl 5.004 or later.


DOCUMENTATION

After installing,  you can find documentation for these modules  with
the perldoc command.

    perldoc File::HomeDir::Tiny

Or try using man (it’s faster, in my experience):

    man File::HomeDir::Tiny


